-{"id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","title":"robot-redesign/parity: align SSE and WebSocket behavior with durable attention semantics","description":"Align server-side streaming transports with the same durable attention semantics used elsewhere. This task exists because once attention and digest become restart-safe operator primitives, streaming transports must stop inventing their own event meanings.","design":"The work should ensure SSE and WebSocket streams honor the same cursor, replay, resync, degraded-state, request-correlation, idempotency, aggregation, cooldown, resurfacing, operator-attention-state, action-handoff, and recoverable-error semantics as CLI and REST consumers. It should also decide how stream initialization, backlog replay, and handoff to live updates behave when items are pinned, snoozed, acknowledged, muted, or manually escalated. This task is about semantic alignment, not merely plumbing bytes over a socket.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when streaming transports can be treated as alternative delivery mechanisms for the same durable, deduplicated, operator-shaped, and request-correlated event product rather than as bespoke feeds.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:25.318193079Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T21:09:25.205138353Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["parity","robot-redesign","streaming"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:34.759084751Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:51.524008109Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.8.3","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:00.515239538Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thre