 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9","title":"robot-redesign/validation: tests, docs, transition, and legacy cleanup","description":"Add the deterministic fixtures, unit tests, schema goldens, integration coverage, Go-based E2E drivers, benchmark regressions, documentation refresh, transition notes, and legacy-path removal needed to make the redesign durable instead of aspirational. This epic exists because contract-heavy work only becomes real when behavior is pinned down, debugging is practical, cost regressions are visible, and the old assembly paths are retired safely.","design":"The redesign will touch contracts, SQLite persistence, event replay, explainability, renderers, and multiple transports. That means we need: checked-in example payloads and scenario matrices; shared deterministic Go test harnesses and fault injectors under testdata; package-local _test.go unit suites; integration coverage for persistence, degraded recovery, restart safety, and diagnostic evidence flow; Go-based E2E drivers under e2e/ that exercise CLI, REST, and streaming parity with verbose logging of commands, cursors, schema IDs, source_health, incidents, explainability handles, and assertion diffs; benchmark and regression coverage for payload size, latency, diagnostics cost, and storage churn; and explicit cleanup of superseded paths.\n\nThis epic is where we force the new architecture to become the only architecture, rather than one more parallel layer.","acceptance_criteria":"This epic is complete when deterministic Go-based unit, integration, benchmark, and E2E coverage pin the redesign's contract, ergonomics, explainability, and cost profile with great detailed logging; repository docs are self-contained and point to the example corpus and test entry points; and legacy robot assembly paths have been removed so the shared projection architecture is the only supported path.","notes":"Do not declare success early just because the new snapshot output looks good once. The bar is parity, restart safety, contract stability, comprehensive automated verification, and removal of redundant logic. Validation beads are part of the architecture, not optional QA garnish.","status":"open","priority":4,"issue_type":"epic","estimated_minutes":300,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:13.892254319Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-22T00:12:54.073288880Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:13.892254319Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":321,"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9","author":"ubuntu","text":"Future self: the cleanup work is part of the feature, not optional janitorial follow-up.","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:32:14Z"}]}
 {"id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","title":"robot-redesign/validation: add schema goldens and contract stability tests","description":"Add golden tests and contract stability checks for robot payload schemas, checked-in example payloads, and registry-backed discovery output. This task exists because the redesign only improves long-term quality if contract drift becomes obvious and explainable.","design":"The tests should pin checked-in schema artifacts, normative example payloads and scenario transcripts, registry-generated capabilities/help/schema views, representative payload shapes for core surfaces, canonical error or remediation examples for invalid cursor, resync-required, bounded-result, duplicate-request, and invalid-inspect conditions, request identity or idempotency examples, correlated actuation outcomes, operator-attention-state examples such as acknowledge or snooze or pin transitions, and diagnostic explainability examples such as explanation-handle shapes, evidence summaries, suppression markers, and why-this-is-stale or truncated flows. They should make breaking changes explicit, keep additive changes disciplined, and log schema IDs, example names, changed sections, error codes, request or outcome IDs, operator-state markers, diagnostic handles, and high-signal diffs when goldens move. The focus is not on testing every field serializer in isolation; it is on safeguarding the declared contract and its concrete examples.","acceptance_criteria":"This task is complete when schema, example, and discovery drift trigger obvious test failures with rich diagnostics, and maintainers can evolve the robot contract only through explicit intentional updates to schemas and examples, including retry-safe, attention-hygiene, and operator-override semantics.","notes":"Use the example corpus as an executable contract, not as a bag of arbitrary snapshots.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","estimated_minutes":180,"created_at":"2026-03-21T23:38:26.297471362Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-26T19:44:58.856192131Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["robot-redesign","schema","validation"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.10","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:23:35.335731985Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:29:52.264294078Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:48:01.309834452Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.13","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:26:01.211338268Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T01:36:19.931830708Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.5","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:48:15.728838931Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.6","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:57:25.868389436Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:02:38.566794194Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.1.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-22T00:17:54.239112622Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-21T23:40:14.153996914Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-j9jo3.9.1","depends_on_id":"bd-j9jo3.6.2","type":"blocks"