 {"id":"bd-rcwdt","title":"Task: Implement --robot-ensemble-synthesize for triggering synthesis","description":"# Task: Implement --robot-ensemble-synthesize for triggering synthesis\n\nTrigger Stage 3 synthesis for an ensemble session via robot mode.\n\n## Command Specification\n```bash\nntm --robot-ensemble-synthesize=SESSION \\\n  --strategy=manual|adversarial|consensus|creative|analytical|deliberative|prioritized|dialectical|meta-reasoning|voting|argumentation-graph \\\n  --format=markdown|json|yaml \\\n  --output=/path/to/report.md \\\n  --force\n```\n\n## Behavior\n1. Validate ensemble session exists and outputs collected\n2. If outputs incomplete and `--force` not set, return error\n3. Run OutputCollector + Synthesizer + DisagreementAuditor\n4. Emit deterministic formatted output (markdown/json/yaml)\n5. Return audit summary + output path\n\n## Response Schema\n```json\n{\n  \"success\": true,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-01-23T10:30:00Z\",\n  \"action\": \"ensemble_synthesize\",\n  \"session\": \"arch-review-2024-01-15\",\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"strategy\": \"adversarial\",\n  \"report\": {\n    \"summary\": \"...\",\n    \"output_path\": \"/tmp/ensemble_report.md\",\n    \"findings_count\": 12,\n    \"recommendations_count\": 7\n  },\n  \"audit\": {\n    \"conflict_count\": 5,\n    \"unresolved\": 2,\n    \"high_conflict_pairs\": [\"A1↔E2\"]\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Error Codes\n- ENSEMBLE_NOT_FOUND\n- SYNTHESIS_NOT_READY (outputs incomplete)\n- OUTPUT_SCHEMA_INVALID\n- INTERNAL_ERROR\n\n## Logging Requirements\n- Log start/end time and strategy\n- Log number of outputs collected + invalid outputs\n- Log audit conflict counts\n\n## File Location\ninternal/robot/ensemble_synthesize.go\n\n## Dependencies\n- OutputCollector (bd-1av7i)\n- Synthesis system (bd-2qwm8)\n- DisagreementAuditor (bd-38go8)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-23T07:41:04.554611187Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-28T20:58:19.853721727Z","closed_at":"2026-01-28T20:58:19.853638883Z","close_reason":"Implemented --robot-ensemble-synthesize command with strategy, format, output, and force options","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-rcwdt","depends_on_id":"bd-1av7i","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-28T22:40:02Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-rcwdt","depends_on_id":"bd-2qwm8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-28T22:40:02Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-rcwdt","depends_on_id":"bd-38go8","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-28T22:40:02Z","created_by":"import","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-rjlw","title":"Error Handling Tests: Recovery failure scenarios","description":"## Error Handling Tests for Session Recovery\n\n### Error Scenarios\n1. **Tmux not running**\n   - Test recovery when tmux server not started\n   - Verify clear error message\n\n2. **Corrupted state files**\n   - Invalid JSON in state file\n   - Missing required fields\n   - State file permissions denied\n\n3. **Pane recreation failures**\n   - Target window doesn't exist\n   - Shell command fails\n   - Insufficient terminal size\n\n4. **Agent Mail unavailable**\n   - Recovery without Agent Mail MCP\n   - File reservations cannot be restored\n\n### Graceful Degradation\n- Test recovery continues despite individual pane failures\n- Test state file backup before overwrite\n- Test rollback on catastrophic failure\n\n### Logging\nlog.Printf(\"[RECOVERY-ERROR] Failed to restore pane %s: %v\", paneName, err)\nlog.Printf(\"[RECOVERY-FALLBACK] Using degraded mode: %s\", reason)\nlog.Printf(\"[RECOVERY-CLEANUP] Rolling back: %s\", action)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-19T06:12:55.829694512Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-19T22:56:26.983073664Z","closed_at":"2026-01-19T22:56:26.982679452Z","close_reason":"Created comprehensive error handling tests for recovery failure scenarios in internal/checkpoint/recovery_errors_test.go. Tests cover: corrupted state files (malformed JSON, empty files, invalid structure, missing fields, null values), scrollback file errors (file not found, permission denied), restorer error conditions (nil checkpoint, empty session, permission issues), validation scenarios (git branch mismatch, custom directory override, missing scrollbacks), graceful degradation (warning collection, invalid checkpoint skipping, partial state), and edge cases (zero values, special characters, logging verification). All 30+ new tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-rjlw","depends_on_id":"bd-1ed7","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-01-19T06:19:23.969432300Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-rjlw","depends_on_id":"bd-38kx","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-19T06:12:55.851078579Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
 {"id":"bd-rmnfk","title":"Task: Evaluate TOON vs JSON on NTM robot payloads","description":"## Overview\nMeasure TOON vs JSON for typical NTM robot outputs (status, snapshot, context, assign) to decide default policy.\n\n## Inputs (sample payloads)\n- `ntm --robot-status`\n- `ntm --robot-snapshot`\n- `ntm --robot-context`\n- `ntm --robot-plan` / `--robot-graph` (BV integration)\n\n## Method\n1. Capture representative JSON payloads from each command.\n2. Encode to TOON using the `toon` CLI (if available) with `--delimiter \"\\t\"`.\n3. Optionally test `--keyFolding safe` on deeply nested payloads.\n4. Compute token counts using NTM’s token estimator (same tokenizer assumptions used elsewhere).\n5. Compare size, readability, and failure modes (e.g., truncation detection).\n\n## Decision Criteria\n- If TOON saves ≥25% tokens on common payloads with no parsing downsides, allow TOON default via config or `auto`.\n- If savings are marginal or tooling risk is high, keep JSON default but document TOON for LLM‑only usage.\n\n## Output\n- Short report in notes with token counts and recommendation for default policy.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- At least 4 payloads measured\n- Token counts recorded for JSON vs TOON\n- Explicit default recommendation","notes":"## Evaluation Results\n\n### Token Efficiency Measurements\n| Payload | JSON | TOON | Savings |\n|---------|------|------|---------|\n| StatusOutput (3 sessions) | ~542 | ~287 | 47% |\n| SessionInfo array | ~374 | ~198 | 47% |\n| TokenBreakdown array | ~100 | ~36 | 64% |\n| PlanActions array | ~168 | ~106 | 37% |\n| AgentInfo array | ~225 | ~98 | 56% |\n| Simple RobotResponse | ~17 | ~23 | -35% |\n| Error response | ~50 | ~41 | 18% |\n\n### Summary\nTotal: JSON ~1,476 tokens → TOON ~789 tokens = **46.5% savings**\n\n### Recommendation\nTOON saves ≥25% tokens. Allow TOON as default via config or auto mode.\n\nTest: internal/robot/toon_eval_test.go","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-01-19T19:13:42.222345943Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-01-20T18:22:46.421146100Z","closed_at":"2026-01-20T18:22:46.421057062Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-rmnfk","depends_on_id":"bd-2dovu","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-01-19T19:13:42.250887571Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
